<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 14:55:42 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>大黄蜂可以即时解决问题，为昆虫的令人印象深刻的认知能力增添了色彩</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/bumblebees-can-solve-problems-on-the-fly-adding-to-the-insects-list-of-impressive-cognitive-abilities-180988925/</link><description>在一系列实验中，模糊传粉者弄清楚了如何使用球作为获取含糖食物的工具。这项研究进一步强调，尽管这些生物的大脑很小，但它们却相当聪明</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/bumblebees-can-solve-problems-on-the-fly-adding-to-the-insects-list-of-impressive-cognitive-abilities-180988925/</guid></item><item><title>500 年前，列奥纳多·达·芬奇的笔记本被切碎并分离。现在，发明人的手稿和图纸在在线档案中被重建</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/500-years-ago-da-vincis-notebook-was-cut-up-and-separated-now-the-inventors-manuscripts-and-drawings-are-reconstructed-in-an-online-archive-180988922/</link><description>伽利略博物馆研究人员开发的一种新工具恢复了几个世纪前切除的碎片中的 50 页</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 02:35:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/500-years-ago-da-vincis-notebook-was-cut-up-and-separated-now-the-inventors-manuscripts-and-drawings-are-reconstructed-in-an-online-archive-180988922/</guid></item><item><title>NASA 宣布阿耳忒弥斯 3 号机组人员包括四名宇航员，他们将在近地轨道“承担经过计算的风险”，为未来登月铺平道路</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-announces-the-crew-of-artemis-3-four-astronauts-who-will-take-calculated-risks-in-low-earth-orbit-and-pave-the-way-for-a-future-moon-landing-180988920/</link><description>该任务预计将于明年发射，将练习与 SpaceX 和 Blue Origin 开发的月球着陆器会面和对接</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 20:53:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-announces-the-crew-of-artemis-3-four-astronauts-who-will-take-calculated-risks-in-low-earth-orbit-and-pave-the-way-for-a-future-moon-landing-180988920/</guid></item><item><title>这枚罕见而复杂的胸针代表了罗马帝国征服苏格兰的漫长而杂乱的尝试</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-rare-intricate-brooch-represents-the-roman-empires-long-disjointed-attempt-to-conquer-scotland-180988923/</link><description>这件“微型杰作”将在即将举行的展览中展出，该展览的重点是罗马在被称为喀里多尼亚的高地留下的遗产</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 19:55:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-rare-intricate-brooch-represents-the-roman-empires-long-disjointed-attempt-to-conquer-scotland-180988923/</guid></item><item><title>一项新的研究表明，不同文化背景的人们都认为女性的面孔比男性的面孔更具吸引力</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/people-across-cultures-find-womens-faces-to-be-more-attractive-than-mens-a-new-study-suggests-180988914/</link><description>在许多野生动物物种中，雄性比雌性具有更华丽的特征，以帮助它们吸引配偶。但科学家们很早就注意到，人类似乎是个例外，女性常常被认为是“更公平的性别”</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 19:14:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/people-across-cultures-find-womens-faces-to-be-more-attractive-than-mens-a-new-study-suggests-180988914/</guid></item><item><title>“可爱的小家伙”：科学家在加拉帕戈斯群岛发现了一种蓝色的小章鱼</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cute-little-guy-scientists-discover-a-tiny-blue-species-of-octopus-by-the-galapagos-islands-180988919/</link><description>这种手掌大小的生物是在十多年前的一次研究探险中发现并收集的，但科学家们刚刚将其鉴定为以前未描述过的物种</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 18:33:26 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cute-little-guy-scientists-discover-a-tiny-blue-species-of-octopus-by-the-galapagos-islands-180988919/</guid></item><item><title>澳大利亚当局破纪录地查获了超过 100,000 只非法外来蟑螂</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/more-than-100000-illegal-exotic-cockroaches-were-seized-by-australian-authorities-in-a-record-setting-bug-bust-180988913/</link><description>据澳大利亚气候变化、能源、环境和水部称，这些昆虫的价值估计高达 141,000 美元。外来蟑螂可能危害该国的野生动物和农业</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/more-than-100000-illegal-exotic-cockroaches-were-seized-by-australian-authorities-in-a-record-setting-bug-bust-180988913/</guid></item><item><title>巨石阵的祭坛石是如何获得的？新研究加剧了人类活动与冰川运输之间的争论</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-did-stonehenge-get-its-altar-stone-new-research-reveals-evidence-adding-to-the-debate-between-human-effort-and-glacier-transport-180988918/</link><description>冰流模型和地质分析表明，在上一个冰河时代，冰川可能携带着这块石头走了一段路。然而，科学家表示这种情况不太可能发生</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 22:33:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-did-stonehenge-get-its-altar-stone-new-research-reveals-evidence-adding-to-the-debate-between-human-effort-and-glacier-transport-180988918/</guid></item><item><title>踪迹相机照片捕捉到肯尼亚森林中的稀有羚羊，保护主义者曾担心它们已经消失</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/trail-camera-photos-capture-rare-antelopes-in-a-kenya-forest-where-conservationists-once-feared-they-had-vanished-180988904/</link><description>据信野外生活的山地邦戈鼓不足 100 只，新发现揭示了这种极度濒危生物的重要栖息地</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 20:38:19 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/trail-camera-photos-capture-rare-antelopes-in-a-kenya-forest-where-conservationists-once-feared-they-had-vanished-180988904/</guid></item><item><title>这些意大利青少年在学校过夜。他们在地下室发现了古罗马遗址</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-italian-teenagers-stayed-overnight-at-their-school-they-found-ancient-roman-ruins-hidden-in-the-basement-180988917/</link><description>罗马一所高中的学生偶然发现了一栋保存完好的别墅，其历史可以追溯到公元二世纪中叶。最终，考古学家希望向公众开放这片广阔的空间</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 20:01:05 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-italian-teenagers-stayed-overnight-at-their-school-they-found-ancient-roman-ruins-hidden-in-the-basement-180988917/</guid></item><item><title>NASA 实验性 X-59 飞机首次飞行速度超过音速，为“安静”超音速飞机奠定了基础</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-first-nasas-experimental-x-59-plane-flew-faster-than-the-speed-of-sound-setting-the-stage-for-quiet-supersonic-aircraft-180988916/</link><description>1973 年，美国禁止超音速飞行飞越其陆地上空，因为超音速飞行会产生震耳欲聋的音爆。专家们正在建造一架飞机，它应该以这样的速度飞行，但只会产生轻微的撞击声</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 20:00:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-first-nasas-experimental-x-59-plane-flew-faster-than-the-speed-of-sound-setting-the-stage-for-quiet-supersonic-aircraft-180988916/</guid></item><item><title>约翰·列侬帮助披头士乐队创作的绘画被重新发现，成为摇滚乐的第一批音乐视频之一</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/rediscovered-drawings-john-lennon-helped-create-for-the-beatles-became-one-of-rock-n-rolls-first-music-videos-180988915/</link><description>一位英国收藏家在拍卖会上获得了十幅图画，并将它们借给利物浦披头士博物馆进行临时展览</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 19:33:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/rediscovered-drawings-john-lennon-helped-create-for-the-beatles-became-one-of-rock-n-rolls-first-music-videos-180988915/</guid></item><item><title>哪些模因值得数字化保存？查看英国电影学院为新档案馆选择的在线视频</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/which-memes-deserve-digital-preservation-see-the-online-videos-the-british-film-institute-selected-for-a-new-archive-180988912/</link><description>档案管理员说，几十年来制作的病毒视频、教程、视频博客和直播片段提供了对现代文化和交流的洞察。如果不努力保存，该材料可能会丢失</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 18:04:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/which-memes-deserve-digital-preservation-see-the-online-videos-the-british-film-institute-selected-for-a-new-archive-180988912/</guid></item><item><title>来认识一下“女巫鳄鱼”吧，这是一种奇怪的古代鳄鱼近亲，有两条腿，没有牙齿，在三叠纪时期在新墨西哥州漫游</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-the-witch-croc-a-strange-ancient-crocodile-relative-with-two-legs-and-no-teeth-that-roamed-new-mexico-during-the-triassic-180988909/</link><description>这种爬行动物是一种长得像恐龙的舒沃龙，它代表了一项期待已久的发现，有助于古生物学家填补化石记录中的空白</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 16:09:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-the-witch-croc-a-strange-ancient-crocodile-relative-with-two-legs-and-no-teeth-that-roamed-new-mexico-during-the-triassic-180988909/</guid></item><item><title>这种色彩缤纷的鹦鹉在过去的一个世纪里只见过一次。观鸟者刚刚在未开发的印度尼西亚森林中重新发现了它</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-colorful-parakeet-had-been-seen-only-once-over-the-past-century-birders-just-rediscovered-it-in-an-unexplored-indonesian-forest-180988907/</link><description>蓝额澳洲鹦鹉于 20 年代首次通过七个标本被描述，自 2014 年以来就再也没有被发现过。最近徒步旅行的观鸟者拍摄了这种稀有鸟类的照片，并捕捉到了第一批已知的其叫声的录音</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-colorful-parakeet-had-been-seen-only-once-over-the-past-century-birders-just-rediscovered-it-in-an-unexplored-indonesian-forest-180988907/</guid></item><item><title>一艘“几乎难以置信”的沉船令挪威考古学家震惊，船上装满了完好无损的瓷器和奢侈品</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-shipwreck-almost-beyond-belief-stunned-archaeologists-in-norway-with-its-cargo-of-intact-porcelain-dishes-and-luxury-goods-180988910/</link><description>到目前为止，考古学家已从这艘 18 世纪的沉船中发现了 40 件文物，可能还会发现数千件宝藏</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 22:07:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-shipwreck-almost-beyond-belief-stunned-archaeologists-in-norway-with-its-cargo-of-intact-porcelain-dishes-and-luxury-goods-180988910/</guid></item><item><title>银河系中心的超大质量黑洞似乎在吹风——正如科学家长期以来的理论那样</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-supermassive-black-hole-at-the-heart-of-our-galaxy-seems-to-be-blowing-wind-just-as-scientists-long-theorized-180988908/</link><description>自 20 世纪 70 年代以来，科学家们一直在寻找这种微风的证据。他们已经看到来自其他黑洞的强烈风，但他们一直在努力观察银河系中心的黑洞</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 19:34:01 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-supermassive-black-hole-at-the-heart-of-our-galaxy-seems-to-be-blowing-wind-just-as-scientists-long-theorized-180988908/</guid></item><item><title>这座大教堂矗立在巴塞罗那之上已有 144 年历史。中央塔现已竣工，教皇利奥十四世准备访问</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/sagrada-familia-basilica-has-been-rising-above-barcelona-for-144-years-with-its-central-tower-now-complete-pope-leo-XIV-prepares-to-visit-180988906/</link><description>当安东尼·高迪（Antoni Gaudí）对圣家堂（Sagrada Família）提出雄心勃勃的愿景时，他知道自己无法活着看到它的竣工。建筑师去世一百年后，最高的塔已达到顶峰</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 19:14:25 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/sagrada-familia-basilica-has-been-rising-above-barcelona-for-144-years-with-its-central-tower-now-complete-pope-leo-XIV-prepares-to-visit-180988906/</guid></item><item><title>在二战领袖温斯顿·丘吉尔去世后首次举办的英国大型回顾展上，令人惊讶地一睹他的消遣——绘画</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/catch-a-surprising-glimpse-at-wwii-leader-winston-churchills-pastime-painting-at-the-first-major-british-retrospective-since-his-death-180988905/</link><description>伦敦展出的 50 多幅油画详细描述了首相远离战争、演讲和政治的安静时刻</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 17:49:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/catch-a-surprising-glimpse-at-wwii-leader-winston-churchills-pastime-painting-at-the-first-major-british-retrospective-since-his-death-180988905/</guid></item><item><title>科学家研究火蝾螈已有 250 多年的历史。他们刚刚发现这些生物在紫外线下会发光</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-have-been-studying-these-salamanders-for-more-than-250-years-they-just-discovered-the-creatures-glow-under-uv-light-180988900/</link><description>火蝾螈是欧洲研究最深入的两栖动物之一，具有生物荧光，这意味着它们可以吸收外部光源的一种波长的光，然后以另一种波长重新发射光</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 15:09:20 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-have-been-studying-these-salamanders-for-more-than-250-years-they-just-discovered-the-creatures-glow-under-uv-light-180988900/</guid></item></channel></rss>